Have the function NextPalindrome(num) take the num parameter 
being passed and return the next largest palindromic number. 
The input can be any positive integer. For example: if num is 24, 
then your program should return 33 because that is the next 
largest number that is a palindrome. 

def NextPalindrome(num)
	num += 1 
	until Pal?(num)
		num += 1 
	end
	return num 
end

def Pal?(num)
	num.to_s == num.to_s.reverse
end
